        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>
                <date>Nov 2. 1856</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear friend—</p>
            <p>Enclosed I hand you Dft. On <persName>D &amp; Co</persName> for $25.00/100<lb/> for
                collections made for the Occident &amp; the sale<lb/> of some Books. You will
                perceive by annexed<lb/> statement, that I have sent $1.46 more, than I had on
                hand.<lb/> But I shall collect something soon again.</p>
            <p>I will now proceed to render all the news of this<lb/> city within my knowledge,
                coming under the category<lb/> of Jewish affairs.</p>
            <p>The various holidays, just passed, have been<lb/> generally better observed, than I
                have ever witnessed<lb/> here before. The <date>New-Year</date> and <date>Day
                    of<lb/> Atonement</date> have been particularly very uni-<lb/>versally and
                strictly celebrated. On those<lb/> days the places of business of our
                co-<lb/>-religionists, excepting very few, have been<lb/> closed; and the city,
                indeed, <hi rend="underline">bore</hi> the ap-<lb/>-pearance of a suspension of
                trade and its<lb/> wanted vivacity, to a very great extent.<lb/> This need not be
                wondered at since<lb/> the Israelites occupy a very high and im-<lb/>-portant
                position in point of trade and commerce,<lb/> and in respect to influence and
                intelligence.<lb/> I know they stand here second to no body of<lb/> our faith in any
                one city of the <placeName>United-States</placeName>.<lb/> In four different Houses
                of Worship were</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>divine services rendered during the holidays<lb/> and at each on the attendance was
                nu-<lb/>merous.</p>
            <p>The congregation “Emanu El” on <date>New Year</date> for<lb/> the first time,
                introduced a change in the worship, de-<lb/>-viating from the ancient and usual
                mode,<lb/> and partaking somewhat of the reformatory<lb/> character. It consists of
                the establishment<lb/> of an organized choir, accompanied by a<lb/> melodean, and
                some omissions of the usual<lb/> prayers. Some other new regulations were<lb/>
                introduced with a happy result for the<lb/> correction of that disorder tending to
                mar<lb/> the solemnity and decorum during the hours<lb/> of worship, which is so
                universally prevalent<lb/> in our synagogues during divine service.<lb/> The annual
                meeting of this congregation<lb/> (“Emanu El”) for the election of officers
                took<lb/> place on <date>Sunday the 19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of October</date>,
                when<lb/> the following gentlemen were duly elected: for<lb/> President,
                    <persName>L. Tichener</persName>; Vice President, <persName>Saml.
                    Marx</persName>.<lb/> Treasurer, <persName>A. Tandler</persName>; Financial
                Secretary, <persName>M. Frank</persName>;<lb/> Recording Secretary, <persName>David
                    Stern</persName>; Trustees, <persName>H<lb/> Ragensburger</persName>,
                    <persName>H. Seligman</persName>, <persName>L. Strauss</persName>; &amp;
                    <persName>R. Kline</persName>;<lb/> Reader, <persName>G. Messinger</persName>;
                Shamas, <persName>M. Steppacher</persName><lb/> The annual reports, that were
                presented by<lb/> the different officers at this meeting, demonstrate<lb/> that the
                state of this congregation is highly<lb/> prosperous. Since last year the
                spacious<lb/> basement of the synagogue was converted</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>into a school-room, &amp; many other im-<lb/>provements were added to the
                building.<lb/> The congregation “Shearth-Israel” held a<lb/> meeting for the
                election of officers on the<lb/>
                <date>19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of October</date>, which resulted in the
                fol-<lb/>-lowing choice: For Pres. <persName>I. Rich</persName>; Vice Pres.<lb/>
                &amp; Treasurer, <persName>J. P. Davis</persName>; Secret. <persName>B. I.
                    Baruch</persName>;<lb/> Trustees, <persName>M. Martin</persName>, <persName>L.
                    King</persName>, <persName>M. A. Blumenthal</persName>,<lb/>
                <persName>M. B. Ashim</persName> &amp; <persName>T. Shaw</persName>; Shamas
                    <persName>I. Goldsmith</persName><lb/> The sixth anniversary Ball of the
                “Eureka<lb/> Benevolent Society” took place on the <date>22nd<lb/> of
                October</date>, by which $900.00/100 were added to<lb/> the funds. This society is
                composed of<lb/> a large Number of Members, and through<lb/> their judicious and
                praiseworthy management<lb/> the charitable purposes are successfully
                ac-<lb/>complished, and benevolence is enabled to<lb/> extend a welcome hand to the
                foresaken,<lb/> and soothe the pangs of afflicting poverty<lb/> of the
                unfortunate</p>
            <p>At a meeting of the H.Y.M.M.B. &amp;<lb/> L. Association, held on the <date>5<hi
                        rend="sup">th</hi> of October</date><lb/> the following officers were
                elected for the<lb/> ensuing year: For Pres. <persName>S. Solomons</persName>;<lb/>
                V. Pres. <persName>E. Levey</persName>; Rec. Sec'y. <persName>A.
                Hoffman</persName>;<lb/> Fin. Sec'y. <persName>H. Schmitt</persName>; Treas.
                    <persName>L. Level</persName>; Trustees,<lb/>
                <persName>B. Hoffman</persName>, <persName>L. Kahn</persName>, <persName>B.
                    Simon</persName>, <persName>I. Godcheaux</persName><lb/> Librarian <persName>B.
                    Vagstratter</persName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">I remain Yours truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">Cauffman H Meyers</persName>
            </p>
